Introduction:
 Who is Veneziano Coffee Roasters? 

 We’re a progressive, dynamic and pioneering coffee roasting business with passion and drive, energised by the shared ambitions of our team and coffee community. Within our industry, the Veneziano name is synonymous with knowledge, experience, and innovation. 


Description:
 What's the Opportunity? 

 If you’re after a hands-on Warehouse-based role in a busy, dynamic and welcoming business located in handy West End then keep reading… 

 The West End Driver and Team Allrounder will primarily execute delivery and distribution tasks and provide support for the Operations team across Warehousing and Production tasks when not on the road. 

 What skills and knowledge do I need? 

 We'd love someone with previous experience in a FMCG warehousing and dispatch environment but ultimately we're after someone who is reliable, physically fit, and results-driven as well as being able to work independently and in a team environment. 

 Experience with NetSuite or similar ERP is very advantageous. 

 As this is a customer-facing delivery role, it is crucial that the succesful candiate has a customer-first attitude, and a full driver's licence. A forklift licence is also desirable. 


In addition to this, our successful candidate will also:


 Love customer service and want to build a rapport with people and our customers; 
 The ability to go beyond delivery goods by developing relationships and promote our brand; 
 Have pride in their apperance and the brand; 
 Have great time management, communication and organisational skills; 
 Highly motivated with the ability to multitask and complete assignments within time constraints, deadlines and priorities. 
 You will be responsible for the following; 



 Delivering fresh coffee to customers using the company van; 
 Accurate picking of stock; 
 Checking and inspecting goods received and dispatched and ensuring they are of accurate and of acceptable quality; 
 Maintain the cleanliness of the company van; 
 Communicate any customer issues to customer service; 
 Deliver goods in a safe and timely manner; 
 Receiving, moving, checking and storing incoming goods; 
 Packing and labelling products, such as coffee for dispatch; 
 Picking, packing and preparing goods for delivery; 
 Loading and unloading delivery vans, and dispatch courier trucks; 
 Stock rotation; 
 Assisting the team in weekly cleaning and maintenance schedules. 

What we’re offering:
 This opportunity gives you the chance to join a tight-knit team and growing business where you opportunities for growth and development are uncapped. With a focus on work-life balance, a company that genuinely cares about your wellbeing, and the stability of a business that continues to expand and thrive. In addition to this we offer: 



 Being part of a strong global business with expansion plans; 
 The opportunity to join a business with a focus on sustainability and well-being; 
 Generous discounts on coffee, coffee equipment, and at leading cafes; 
 Quarterly and EOY staff appreciation program; 
 Access to our Employee Assistance Program; 
 Most importantly - Work/life balance; 
 Paid Parental Leave and Paid Volunteer Time Off 
 Employee Wellbeing Program 
 If this sounds like you, send us an application with a cover letter telling us a bit about yourself plus a resume detailing your relevant experience. 

 There is plenty of opportunity for you to make your mark at Veneziano Coffee Roasters. 

 Inspired to be a part of the journey? Click apply now.
